Cloudflare Account         — Control boundary
 ├─ Identity & Access      — Account security
 │   ├─ User               — Human login
 │   ├─ API Token          — Programmatic access
 │   ├─ Permissions        — Allowed scope
 │   └─ Audit Logs         — Activity trail
 │
 ├─ DNS Layer              — Target discovery
 │   ├─ Zone               — Domain ownership
 │   ├─ DNS Records        — IP exposure
 │   ├─ Proxy Status       — Orange/Gray cloud
 │   └─ TTL                — Cache behavior
 │
 ├─ Edge Network           — First contact surface
 │   ├─ Anycast IP         — Global entry point
 │   ├─ POP                — Edge location
 │   ├─ TLS Termination    — Encryption boundary
 │   └─ HTTP Parsing       — Request handling
 │
 ├─ Security Layer         — Filtering & defense
 │   ├─ WAF                — Request inspection
 │   ├─ Firewall Rules     — IP / ASN / Geo rules
 │   ├─ Rate Limiting      — Abuse control
 │   ├─ Bot Management     — Automation detection
 │   └─ DDoS Protection    — Traffic absorption
 │
 ├─ Application Layer      — Main attack surface
 │   ├─ HTTP / HTTPS       — Transport protocol
 │   ├─ REST API           — Endpoint exposure
 │   │   ├─ Path           — URL structure
 │   │   ├─ Method         — GET / POST / PUT
 │   │   ├─ Headers        — Metadata input
 │   │   └─ Body           — JSON / Form payload
 │   │
 │   └─ Origin Logic       — Backend behavior
 │
 ├─ Edge Compute           — Execution boundary
 │   ├─ Workers            — Serverless code
 │   ├─ Durable Objects    — Stateful logic
 │   └─ Cron Triggers      — Scheduled execution
 │
 ├─ Origin Infrastructure  — Hidden backend
 │   ├─ Load Balancer      — Traffic routing
 │   ├─ Origin IP          — Real server address
 │   ├─ Cloud / On‑prem    — Hosting environment
 │   └─ Private Network    — Bypass target
 │
 ├─ Data Layer             — High‑value assets
 │   ├─ KV                 — Key‑value storage
 │   ├─ R2                 — Object storage
 │   ├─ D1                 — SQL database
 │   └─ Secrets            — Sensitive config
 │
 ├─ Networking Services    — Lateral paths
 │   ├─ Tunnel (cloudflared)— Origin exposure
 │   ├─ Zero Trust         — Access control plane
 │   └─ Spectrum           — TCP/UDP proxying
 │
 └─ Observability          — Detection surface
     ├─ Logs               — Request visibility
     ├─ Analytics          — Traffic patterns
     └─ Alerts             — Security signals

